  "prompt": "Who is the speaker of Rajya Sabha?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, the **Chairperson of the Rajya Sabha** (the upper house of India's Parliament) is the **Vice President of India**, **Jagdeep Dhankhar**. \n\n### Key Points:\n- **Rajya Sabha Leadership**: Unlike the Lok Sabha (the lower house), which is presided over by the Speaker, the Rajya Sabha is chaired by the Vice President of India.\n- **Current Chairperson**: **Jagdeep Dhankhar** has been serving as the Vice President and thus the Chairperson of the Rajya Sabha since August 11, 2022.\n- **Deputy Chairman**: Assisting the Chairperson is the **Deputy Chairman of the Rajya Sabha**, a position currently held by **Mallikarjun Kharge** (please verify as this may have changed).\n\nIf you were referring to the Speaker of the Lok Sabha or need information on other parliamentary positions, feel free to ask!",
